  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. The second equation is exactly three times the first, so both represent the same line. Solving 3x - 4y = 12 for y: 4y = 3x - 12, so y = (3x - 12)/4. For x = r, the point (r, (3r - 12)/4) lies on the line. The other choices use incorrect rearrangements (e.g., flipping a sign or swapping coefficients).</p>",
